On 4/17/03 9:05 PM, "Steve Pribyl" <steve(-at-)unliketea.com> wrote:

> I want to go to my local Junk Yard to get some body pannels.  Can anyone
> recomend some portable cutters to remove bits.  Thinks of wheel well parts
> rear corners, pedistals.
> 
> Thanks
> Steve


18 or 24 volt sawzall and at least 2 batteries, and some good bimetal
blades. I can't see doing much cutting with hand tools, especially where the
panels have lots of relief, they will nearly impossible to get through with
hand cutters.

Scott Lyons
